      "The ankles and calves are Aquarius's primary physical vulnerabilities — sprains, strains, and circulatory problems in the lower legs are disproportionately common. The circulatory system more broadly is an area of concern: varicose veins, poor circulation, and irregular heartbeat can affect this sign, particularly during periods of stress. The nervous system is a major vulnerability: anxiety, insomnia, and nervous tension accumulate when Aquarius's overactive mind doesn't get adequate rest. Muscle cramps, restless leg syndrome, and sudden, unpredictable health events (reflecting Uranus's sudden nature) are characteristic patterns. They may also be prone to some autoimmune conditions, as the immune system — which must distinguish self from non-self — resonates with Aquarius's themes of individuality and group identity.",

